<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-8943] Move SecurityProviderCreator to a public package</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8943</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The public interface `SecurityProviderCreator` added under &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8669&quot; title=&quot;Add java security providers in Kafka Security config&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-8669&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-8669&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (KIP-492) is currently in the internal package `org.apache.kafka.common.security` along with other internal classes. Since this is a public interface, we should move it to a public package. We should also add `@InterfaceStability.Evolving` annotation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Marked as blocker for 2.4.0 since we should do this before the release.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
